Just shy of 36” it was an epic fight on the green @darkmatterfishing psychedelic spinning rod paired with a 4000-C @daiwausa Ballistic MQ LT. Bite has been pretty hot out on the flats on the IRL. But the fish have been spooky in the clear water. I got these two #snook by positioning myself out about 100 yards from where I knew some fish were holding. I tail hooked my bait and let them swim out naturally into the strike zone and that did it. Casting in I only spooked the fish even with a perfect leading cast. Exhilarating fights on light tackle and a cool video to come soon 🎥 on #youtube #florida #fishing #bigfish #fishaholic #saltlife #floridalife

Epic bite and fight to catch this one! It’s not a monster but a healthy 22 pounder that crushed the mullet on some extremely light tackle! This jetty was a life saver!! A freak rain squall blew over me while out on the water in #northcarolina it wasn’t in the forecast. Saw it develop in the distance and on radar and I had two decisions. 1. wait it out near the shelter of the jetty.  Or 2. go around the jetty and straight at the storm to race to shore before it hit. In a kayak speed isn’t your greatest strength. Therefore, I chose to wade it out and I’m glad I did. The wind, waves, and swell at full force on the other side of the jetty would have been very unforgiving. #storm #video #clip #reel #fishaholic #fishing #hobie #kayakfishing

Stoked to surprisingly catch my first #traíra out of a little pond on the side of the highway in #brazil #brazil After driving a lot with my family and my girl @karysteps and her family. We stopped to get lunch halfway into our 5hr drive. Luckily there was a small pond next to the restaurant and @karysteps asked “aren’t you going to fish?” I actually said “I don’t think so if we’re in a rush to get to Ilhabela” but she said “you have time!” So I ran to the car rigged up this little spinner bait and @zmanfishingproducts swimbait combo and slowly swam this through the dirty pea soup colored water and got slammed shortly after by my first Traíra!!!! I wasn’t filming and I didn’t have my phone so I’m very thankful I have a great girl to run over and help to capture a short video and picture!!!

Hot Tarpon bite this weekend! 🔥. Generally these Tarpon bite in this spot between sunrise and the latest 10 Am if the tide is right. The sunrise early morning bite was non-existent and I thought it was not going to happen. Especially with the boat traffic increasing every minute because it was Saturday. But luckily the current got just right from 8:45 to 10 Am and with large mullet I trolled up six nice Tarpon to eat and I landed two 💪🏻 caught this nice fish on the @darkmatterfishing fishaholic 7’ heavy action inshore spinning rod paired with a 12000 baitrunner. 
.
.
